# Cyber Defense: Threat Hunting, Incident Response & DFIR

In this project, we simulate a full incident response lifecycle — from initial threat hunt through forensic analysis, incident reporting, and eradication — against a compromised Azure Windows VM running an exposed MySQL server and RDP endpoint.

_**Inception State:**_ A suspicious host is flagged. No investigation has been performed, no attacker actions are known, and the system is still fully exposed to the internet.

_**Completion State:**_ The full attack chain is reconstructed across MySQL audit logs and Defender Advanced Hunting telemetry, a formal NIST SP 800-61r2 incident report is produced, MDE investigation packages are forensically compared (pre vs. post), and all eradication and recovery steps are completed.

