### Phase 1 — Threat Hunting CTF (Foundational Skills)

Before investigating a real incident, core threat hunting skills are developed through a structured Capture-the-Flag exercise against host `npt-ws01`. The exercise simulates a full intrusion chain — credential brute-force, remote code execution, C2 beaconing, persistence, and lateral movement — requiring the analyst to capture 11 flags by querying raw Defender telemetry.

**Skills developed:** authentication analysis, process chain reconstruction, C2 identification, registry persistence hunting, scheduled task analysis, lateral movement detection.

